    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the grill to medium-high and boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>sun-dried tomatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped sun-dried tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min</p><p>Add the <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray under the grill for 2-4 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100 ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan with the sun-dried tomatoes, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce is starting to thicken</p><p>While the sauce is thickening, drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta sauce has thickened slightly, add the <strong>drained tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>and <strong>chopped wilted spinach </strong>to the pan and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato sauce with mozzarella & tomato tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato sauce with mozzarella & tomato tortelloni </strong>with the <strong>drained mozzarella </strong>torn over the top</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> toasted flaked almonds </strong>and drizzle everything with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
